## Backend Implementation Details

### 1. `src-backend/src/rag/config.rs`

```rust
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct RagConfig {
    pub embedding: EmbeddingConfig,
    pub chunking: ChunkingConfig,
    pub retrieval: RetrievalConfig,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct EmbeddingConfig {
    pub provider: EmbeddingProvider, // "fastembed" or "llamacpp"
    pub model_name: String,          // e.g. "BGESmallENV15"
    pub batch_size: usize,           // default: 64
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(rename_all = "snake_case")]
pub enum EmbeddingProvider {
    Fastembed,
    LlamaCpp,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct ChunkingConfig {
    pub strategy: ChunkingStrategy,
    pub chunk_size: usize,     // tokens, default: 512
    pub overlap: usize,        // tokens, default: 50
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(rename_all = "snake_case")]
pub enum ChunkingStrategy {
    Fixed,
    Sentence,
    Recursive,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct RetrievalConfig {
    pub top_k: usize,                  // default: 5
    pub similarity_threshold: f32,     // default: 0.3
    pub max_context_tokens: usize,     // default: 4000
    pub query_rewrite: bool,           // default: false
    pub show_sources: bool,            // default: true
}

impl Default for RagConfig {
    // sensible defaults as above
}
```

Persisted to `{data_dir}/rag/config.json`. Load in `main.rs` at startup.

### 2. `src-backend/src/rag/ingestion.rs`

**File parsers** — keep it simple, start with what works:
- `.txt`, `.md` → read as UTF-8 (use `encoding_rs` for detection)
- `.pdf` → use `pdf-extract` crate
- `.csv` → use `csv` crate, each row becomes a chunk
- `.html` → use `scraper` crate, extract text nodes

**Chunking** — one function with strategy dispatch:

```rust
pub fn chunk_text(text: &str, config: &ChunkingConfig) -> Vec<Chunk>
```

- `Fixed`: split into `chunk_size`-char windows with `overlap`-char overlap.
- `Sentence`: split on `.!?\n`, accumulate sentences until near `chunk_size`.
- `Recursive`: split on `["\n\n", "\n", ". ", " "]` hierarchy, each level subdivides the previous when chunks exceed `chunk_size`.

Use a simple whitespace-based token estimator (chars / 4) rather than pulling in a tokenizer crate. Good enough for chunking.

### 3. `src-backend/src/rag/embedding.rs`

```rust
pub trait Embedder: Send + Sync {
    fn embed_batch(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>>;
    fn dimension(&self) -> usize;
}

// --- Backend A: fastembed (default, zero-config) ---
pub struct FastembedEmbedder {
    model: fastembed::TextEmbedding,
    dim: usize,
}

impl FastembedEmbedder {
    pub fn new(model_name: fastembed::EmbeddingModel) -> Result<Self> {
        let model = TextEmbedding::try_new(
            InitOptions::new(model_name).with_show_download_progress(true),
        )?;
        // dimension determined by model
    }
}

// --- Backend B: llama.cpp /v1/embeddings ---
pub struct LlamaCppEmbedder {
    client: reqwest::Client,
    base_url: String,
}
// POST to {base_url}/v1/embeddings with {"input": [...], "model": "..."}
```

**`fastembed` is synchronous** — wrap in `tokio::task::spawn_blocking` when called from async context.

### 4. `src-backend/src/rag/vectorstore.rs`

Use `hnsw_rs` with cosine distance from `anndists`:

```rust
use hnsw_rs::prelude::*;
use anndists::dist::DistCosine;

pub struct VectorStore {
    collections: HashMap<String, Collection>,
    base_path: PathBuf,
}

pub struct Collection {
    pub id: String,
    pub name: String,
    pub dimension: usize,
    hnsw: Hnsw<f32, DistCosine>,
    // Maps hnsw internal DataId → chunk_id (String)
    id_map: Vec<String>,
}

impl VectorStore {
    pub fn create_collection(&mut self, name: &str, dim: usize) -> Result<String>;
    pub fn delete_collection(&mut self, id: &str) -> Result<()>;
    pub fn add_vectors(&mut self, collection_id: &str, chunk_ids: &[String], vectors: &[Vec<f32>]) -> Result<()>;
    pub fn search(&self, collection_id: &str, query: &[f32], top_k: usize) -> Result<Vec<(String, f32)>>; // (chunk_id, score)
    pub fn remove_by_document(&mut self, collection_id: &str, chunk_ids: &[String]) -> Result<()>;
    pub fn persist(&self) -> Result<()>;  // hnsw_rs has built-in dump/reload
    pub fn load(base_path: &PathBuf) -> Result<Self>;
}
```

**Persistence layout:**
```
{data_dir}/rag/collections/{collection_id}/
├── hnsw_graph.bin    # hnsw_rs dump
├── hnsw_data.bin     # hnsw_rs dump
└── id_map.bin        # bincode: Vec<String>
```

