Initialize lazily — if no embedding model is configured yet, these can be `Option<>` and RAG endpoints return 400 until setup.

### 8. `src-backend/src/routes/rag.rs` — API Endpoints

```rust
pub fn rag_router() -> Router<AppState> {
    Router::new()
        // Collections
        .route("/api/rag/collections", post(create_collection).get(list_collections))
        .route("/api/rag/collections/:id", get(get_collection).delete(delete_collection))
        // Documents
        .route("/api/rag/collections/:id/documents", post(upload_documents).get(list_documents))
        .route("/api/rag/collections/:id/documents/:doc_id", delete(delete_document))
        // Search (debug/test)
        .route("/api/rag/collections/:id/search", post(search_collection))
        // Config
        .route("/api/rag/config", get(get_config).put(update_config))
}
```

`upload_documents` handler: accepts `multipart/form-data`, parses files, chunks, embeds (in a background `tokio::spawn` task), stores in vectorstore + SQLite. Return a job ID. Poll status via SSE or polling endpoint.

### 9. Modify Existing Chat Route

In the existing chat completion route (find it in `src-backend/src/routes/`):

- Accept optional `collection_id: Option<String>` in the request body.
- If present, run `RetrievalPipeline::retrieve()` before forwarding to llama.cpp.
- Call `build_rag_messages()` to inject context.
- Append `sources` array to the response JSON.

### 10. `src-backend/src/db/rag.rs` — SQLite Schema

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS rag_collections (
    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    name TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    dimension INTEGER NOT NULL,
    created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS rag_documents (
    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    collection_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES rag_collections(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    filename TEXT NOT NULL,
    file_hash TEXT NOT NULL,  -- SHA-256 for dedup
    file_size INTEGER NOT NULL,
    chunk_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'processing', -- processing | ready | error
    created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS rag_chunks (
    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    document_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES rag_documents(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    collection_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES rag_collections(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    content TEXT NOT NULL,
    chunk_index INTEGER NOT NULL,
    page_number INTEGER,
    token_count INTEGER NOT NULL
);

CREATE INDEX idx_chunks_collection ON rag_chunks(collection_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_chunks_document ON rag_chunks(document_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_documents_collection ON rag_documents(collection_id);
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_documents_hash ON rag_documents(collection_id, file_hash);
```

Embeddings are NOT stored in SQLite — they live in the HNSW index files. Chunk text is in SQLite, retrieved by ID after vector search.

